<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I just happen to believe that life starts at conception.  Since there is not other point at which a logical choice could be made.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You're in luck, so does science <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    I don't think there are many that argue that an embryo isn't alive.  Moss is alive.  Bacteria are alive.  Question is the value placed on an embryo.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Viability? So a child conceived to day is alive before a child conceived 20 years ago becuase our technology improved. Sorry cannot buy it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
?<br>
<br>
They're both alive at conception.<br>
<br>
Are you trying to say that viability is a poor cutoff to choose as a time when abortion is justified because it's a fluid value (the more our technology increases, the earlier an embryo/baby is viable outside the womb)?  I don't see how the fluidity of the number negates the validity of the cutoff, so I'll just disagree with you on this.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>For most people choice should be made before conception. NOTE the use of &quot;MOST&quot; I am not make a complete blanket statement.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
My wife's psycho-ex-husband's sister had about 15 abortions.  She used it as a form of birth control.  She pretty much defines worst case scenario.  Fortunately the powers that be must've gotten ticked because she got a raging infection that destroyed her uterus and now she's infertile.<br>
<br>
While it's very easy to say, in her case, &quot;Ummm... yeah... the only surgery that woman needs is to have her legs superglued together&quot;, that's not a call I want the government making. <br>
<br>
Ultimately, I'm pro-choice, mainly because I don't think the government has any business regulating a woman's reproductive system.  Abortion's a choice I would never recommend someone make, and rather would always counsel someone against if they asked, even if it was the case of rape or something, but I recognize the need for it to remain an option available to women.<br>
<br>
I think embryo's are alive at conception.<br>
I think babies start thinking &amp; learning when they're still in the womb.<br>
But be that as it may, I still think the mother's rights over her own body trump the baby's at least until it's born.<br>
Outlaw of 3rd trimester abortions is a compromise I'd gladly make, if only because it's pretty hard to hit 6 months and not know you're pregnant unless you weigh like 400 pounds.  Plus I think 8 month old fetuses have a much more advanced brain / nervous system than 4 month old fetuses.<br>
<br>
- Ghereth <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bormwarrior>Borm Warrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mod in Kilt!</span><br>  Posts: 603<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/27/03 11:40:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=36>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Freedom of Religion</span><hr size=1> You see Ghereth, to me your position implies a consent to murder. Well intentioned, I give you. You have the welfare of the mother at heart. None the less, if it is alive and is human and you kill it, then it is murder. <br>
